<item>
            <title>[JDK-4912623] GTK L&amp;F: Folder list of the JFileChooser is allowing multiple selection unlike native</title>
                <link>https://bugs.openjdk.org/browse/JDK-4912623</link>
                <project id="10100" key="JDK">JDK</project>
                    <description>Folder list of the JFileChooser is allowing multiple selection unlike native file dialog. Where as the file list does not allow multiple selection.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
Steps to reproduce:&lt;br/&gt;
------------------&lt;br/&gt;
1) Run SwingSet2 on Mercury with -Dswing.gtkthemefile=&amp;lt;Your .gtkrc File&amp;gt;. Change the Look And Feel to GTK.&lt;br/&gt;
2) Go to FileChooser Demo. &lt;br/&gt;
3) Tab to Folder List&lt;br/&gt;
4) Press CTRL+A. It will select all the items in the list. &lt;br/&gt;
5) Now Tab to file list and press ctrl+A, it will not select all the items. &lt;br/&gt;
6) Now Open Gedit.&lt;br/&gt;
7) Click Open. &lt;br/&gt;
8) Repeat the steps 3 to 5. Behaviour for the native will be opposite to its Java counterpart.&lt;br/&gt;
</description>
